assignment this week.

16
00:00:41.545 --> 00:00:44.060
Some possible classes
you might run across

17
00:00:44.060 --> 00:00:47.870
include geographical
entities like Thailand,

18
00:00:47.870 --> 00:00:50.090
organizations like Google,

19
00:00:50.090 --> 00:00:53.110
or geopolitical
entities like Indian.

20
00:00:53.110 --> 00:00:55.445
A few more classes
you might encounter

21
00:00:55.445 --> 00:00:59.105
include time indicators
like the month of December,

22
00:00:59.105 --> 00:01:03.020
artifacts like this
ancient Egyptian statue,

23
00:01:03.020 --> 00:01:05.660
or a person such
as Barack Obama.

24
00:01:05.660 --> 00:01:08.240
As you can see,
named entities can

25
00:01:08.240 --> 00:01:11.030
capture and identify
all kinds of things.

26
00:01:11.030 --> 00:01:13.280
Say you have the
following sentence;

27
00:01:13.280 --> 00:01:16.385
Sharon flew to
Miami last Friday.

28
00:01:16.385 --> 00:01:19.190
A named entity
recognition system would

29
00:01:19.190 --> 00:01:22.430
extract and classify
Sharon as a personal name,

30
00:01:22.430 --> 00:01:25.325
Miami as a geographical entity,

31
00:01:25.325 --> 00:01:28.475
and Friday as a time indicator.

32
00:01:28.475 --> 00:01:30.575
You'll notice that here,

33
00:01:30.575 --> 00:01:33.935
B dash denotes an
entity of some kind,

34
00:01:33.935 --> 00:01:35.690
and all the other words are

35
00:01:35.690 --> 00:01:39.035
classified O, for a filler word.

36
